    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s03.2.13" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f3450003016" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>MAP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The MAP sensor is a variable capacitance sensor. The ECM monitors the MAP signal to determine intake
            manifold pressure (boost). This information is used to control the Exhaust Gas Recirculating (EGR) valve and
            determine fueling calculations. The MAP sensor is installed in the top left side of the intake manifold.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
